{ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "VideoObject", "name": "Protesters clash with police in Nepal after former prime minister arrested", "description": "Protesters took to the streets of the Nepali capital Kathmandu on Saturday after police arrested former Prime Minister Khadga Prasad Oli over the deaths of dozens of people during violent protests in September that toppled the government and resulted in new elections. (AP video shot by: Upendra Man Singh) Subscribe: http://smarturl.it/AssociatedPress Read more: https://apnews.com​ This video may be available for archive licensing via https://newsroom.ap.org/home", "thumbnailUrl": "https://bloximages.chicago2.vip.townnews.com/shorelinemedia.net/content/tncms/assets/v3/editorial/6/60/660f03d7-83c5-5622-90d8-7aab95dc6dc1/69c80040b14c4.preview.jpg?resize=1200%2C675", "uploadDate": "2026-03-28T12:16:21-04:00", "contentUrl": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Icj6WTwZx8g" }

Protesters took to the streets of the Nepali capital Kathmandu on Saturday after police arrested former Prime Minister Khadga Prasad Oli over the deaths of dozens of people during violent protests in September that toppled the government and resulted in new elections. (AP video shot by: Upendra Man Singh)

Subscribe: http://smarturl.it/AssociatedPress

Read more: https://apnews.com​

